# Indigo — AI Coding Rules

## Design System
Full spec: `design-system/indigo/MASTER.md`
Page overrides: `design-system/indigo/pages/{page}.md`

Read MASTER.md before writing any UI code. These are the quick-reference rules:

## Spacing (4px grid)
- Card padding: `p-4`
- Grid gap: `gap-3`
- Section spacing: `space-y-4`
- Layout padding: `p-4 lg:p-6`

## Component Heights
- sm (32px/h-8): DEFAULT for dashboard — buttons, inputs, selects
- Buttons: always `size="sm"`. Never `size="default"` or `size="lg"`.
- Icon buttons: `size="icon-sm"` (32×32)

## Typography (5 sizes)
| Role | Class |
|------|-------|
| Page title | `text-xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.4px]` |
| Section title | `text-sm font-semibold` |
| Body | `text-sm` |
| Caption | `text-xs text-muted-foreground` |
| Badge | `text-[10px] font-medium` |

BANNED: `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-2xl+`, `font-bold`.

## Colors
Use semantic tokens only. Never hardcoded hex, never raw Tailwind colors, never `dark:` overrides.

## Banned Patterns
- Emoji in UI (use Lucide icons)
- `shadow-*` on cards
- `p-6`/`p-8` inside cards
- `outline-none` without focus replacement
- `animate-bounce` for decoration
- Gradients on buttons/cards

## File Conventions
- `"use server"` files → types in sibling `types.ts`
- Auth: `const { user, supabase } = await getAuthenticatedClient()`
- Always verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` = 0 errors
